# üêß Basic Linux/macOS Terminal Commands

> These are essential shell commands for navigating and working in the Terminal on Linux and macOS. The shell used is typically **bash** or **zsh**.

---

## üóÇÔ∏è Navigation

| Command | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `pwd` | Print current working directory |
| `ls` | List files in directory |
| `ls -l` | Long listing format (shows permissions, size, etc.) |
| `ls -a` | Show all files (including hidden) |
| `cd foldername/` | Change directory into folder |
| `cd ..` | Go up one level |
| `cd /` | Go to root directory |
| `cd ~` | Go to home directory |
| `cd -` | Go to previous directory |

---

## üìÅ Files & Directories

| Command | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `mkdir foldername` | Create a new folder |
| `touch filename` | Create an empty file |
| `cp file newfile` | Copy file |
| `cp -r folder newfolder` | Copy folder recursively |
| `mv source target` | Move or rename file/folder |
| `rm file` | Delete file |
| `rm -r folder` | Delete folder and its contents |
| `open filename` | Open file with default app (macOS) |
| `open .` | Open current directory in Finder (macOS) |

---

## üìÑ Viewing Files

| Command | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `cat file` | Print file contents |
| `less file` | View file with scroll (q to quit) |
| `head file` | Show first 10 lines |
| `tail file` | Show last 10 lines |
| `tail -f file` | Live follow changes to file (like logs) |

---

## üõ†Ô∏è File Permissions

| Command | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `chmod +x file.sh` | Make script executable |
| `chmod 755 file` | Set permission (read/write/execute) |
| `chown user:group file` | Change owner of a file |

---

## üì¶ System Info

| Command | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `whoami` | Show current user |
| `uname -a` | System info |
| `top` or `htop` | Live system resource usage |
| `df -h` | Disk space (human readable) |
| `du -sh folder/` | Folder size summary |
| `date` | Show current date and time |
| `uptime` | Show how long the system has been running |

---

## üîç Search

| Command | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `find . -name filename` | Find file recursively |
| `grep "text" file` | Search for text in file |
| `grep -r "text" folder/` | Search recursively |

---

## üîÑ Processes

| Command | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `ps` | Show active processes |
| `ps aux` | Detailed process list |
| `kill PID` | Kill process by PID |
| `kill -9 PID` | Force kill process |
| `&` | Run command in background |
| `ctrl + c` | Cancel/stop running command |
| `ctrl + z` | Suspend running job |
| `jobs` | List background/suspended jobs |
| `fg` | Bring background job to foreground |

---

## üîß Miscellaneous

| Command | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `history` | Show command history |
| `clear` | Clear terminal screen |
| `alias ll='ls -la'` | Create command shortcut (alias) |
| `which command` | Show full path to a command |
| `man command` | Show manual for command |
| `echo "text"` | Print text to terminal |

---

## üìÇ Dotfiles You Should Know

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `.bashrc`, `.zshrc` | Shell config (aliases, env vars, etc.) |
| `.gitconfig` | Git global config |
| `.ssh/` | SSH keys and known hosts |
| `.profile`, `.bash_profile` | Login shell startup files |

---

üß† **Tip**: Use `Tab` for autocompletion, and `‚Üë / ‚Üì` arrows to scroll through past commands!
